mtb_recommendations.KRAS p.G13D Mutation: Based on the tumor profile, no definitive treatment recommendation can be offered.

mtb_recommendations.ATM p.E1666* (4N) Mutation: Perform HRD testing to determine if PARP inhibitors are appropriate, and then add them to the treatment regimen if the patient has not progressed on platinum-based chemotherapy.
mtb_recommendations.ERBB2 amplification: HER2 inhibition with trastuzumab deruxtecan, additional HER2-IHC recommended (evidence level at least m2A, DESTINY-04)
mtb_recommendations.MET amplification: Conduct cMET immunohistochemistry (IHC) to assess cMET expression and consider telisotuzumab vedotin (or alternatively, capmatinib)

mtb_recommendations.PIK3CA p.E545K Mutation (AF 25%): Inclusion in the CRAFT trial (NCT04551521) after failing chemotherapy treatment and alpelisib (PIK3CA inhibitor), PMID: 29401002, PMID: 31091374, PMID: 35133871.

mtb_recommendations.EGFR Mutation: MET amplification is a potential secondary resistance mechanism in EGFR-inhibitor treated patients. If no EGFR inhibitors have been used, consider EGFR inhibition based on the level of MET amplification and clinical progression. However, if resistance is mediated by MET, use EGFR inhibitors with caution (PMID: 34837746).

mtb_recommendations.KRAS p.G12C Mutation (AF 18%): Sotorasib, approved second-line treatment for lung cancer, source: DOI: 10.1056/NEJMoa2103695. Study check nNGM, e.g. KontRASt-01 & -03 (JGQ)

mtb_recommendations.NF1 p.I1605fs Mutation (AF 39%): CR: MEK inhibition with trametinib in NF1 mutated melanoma, PR, m1C, doi: 10.1200/PO.18.00028

mtb_recommendations.FGFR2::BICC1 Fusion: Futibatinib and pemigatinib are approved therapies for this condition (EMA)

mtb_recommendations.TMB Tumor Mutational Burden 10.5 Mut/Mb: Immunotherapy with Pembrolizumab could be explored as a treatment possibility.
mtb_recommendations.HRAS p.Q61R Mutation (AF 44%): Phase II trial, 30 patients with HNSCC, tipifarnib, ORR 55%, mPFS 5.6 months, PMID 33750196
mtb_recommendations.PIK3CA p.E545K Mutation (AF 39%): A case report describes a patient with salivary duct carcinoma (SDC) harboring a PIK3CA mutation and high androgen receptor (AR) expression who achieved a metabolic complete response (CR) with alpelisib and bicalutamide therapy for at least 12 months (m1C, PMID: 34036229, PMID: 29401002; PMID:31091374; PMID: 35133871). PIK3CA mutations may confer a higher risk of developing resistance to HRAS targeted therapies. Consider evaluation for enrolment in the CRAFT study (NCT04551521) after failure of chemotherapy, even if the patient has an HRAS mutation.

mtb_recommendations.EGFR p.E746_A750del Mutation (AF 50%): regimen infiltration by CD8+ T cells. Source: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5762318/
mtb_recommendations.EGFR p.C797S Mutation (AF 29%): Resistance mutation to third-line TKIs. Source: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8724843/
mtb_recommendations.STK11 p.C210* Mutation (AF 39%): The presence of a STK11 p.C210 mutation (AF 39%) suggests the possibility of primary resistance to PD-1 blockade. Source: https://meetings.asco.org/abstracts-presentations/175038
